Components
    Imports of other classes
    A single decorator (always prefaced with an @)
    An exported class
Typescript is a superset of JavaScript
Advantages:
    Provide stronger type checking in dev mode for:
        Properties(variables)
        Method Parameters
        Method Return Values
    Is transpiled (compiled) into JavaScript

Installation of Typescript (Global)
    npm ls typescript -g
    npm install typescript -g
    
Installation of Typescript (LOCAL)
    npm init -y
    npm install typescript -g
    
Initialization of Typescript
    tsc --init
    
Transpilling
    tsc.exe is the transpiler
    turns TypeScript (*.ts) into JavaScript (*.js)

Multiple options 
    tsc hi.ts => hi.js (single convert)
    tsc *.ts => *.js (wildcard convert)

tsconfig.json (in project node)
    compilerOptions
        -outDir: "js"
    include: ["ts/**.*"]

tsc -w (? not sure what this does)
